msgid ""
"|        | ж”ҜжҢҒз»ҙеәҰиҢғеӣҙ          |\n"
"| ------ | --------------- |\n"
"| GPU    | д»…ж”ҜжҢҒ 1~5з»ҙ tensor |\n"
"| Ascend A2/A3 | д»…ж”ҜжҢҒ 1~5з»ҙ tensor |\n"
msgstr ""
"|        | Supported Dimension Range |\n"
"| ------ | ----------------------- |\n"
"| GPU    | Only supports 1~5D tensors |\n"
"| Ascend A2/A3 | Only supports 1~5D tensors |\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Memory_Pointer_Ops/tl.advance.md:28
msgid "з»“и®әпјҡеңЁ Shape ж–№йқўпјҢGPU дёҺ Ascend е№іеҸ°ж— е·®ејӮпјҢеқҮж”ҜжҢҒ 1 иҮі 5 з»ҙеј йҮҸгҖӮ"
msgstr "Conclusion: In terms of Shape, there is no difference between GPU and Ascend platforms; both support tensors from 1 to 5 dimensions."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Memory_Pointer_Ops/tl.advance.md:30
msgid "### 2.3 зү№ж®ҠйҷҗеҲ¶иҜҙжҳҺ"
msgstr "### 2.3 Special Restrictions"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Memory_Pointer_Ops/tl.advance.md:32
msgid "> зӣёеҜ№зӨҫеҢәиғҪеҠӣзјәеӨұдё”ж— жі•е®һзҺ°"
msgstr "> Relative community capability deficiency and inability to achieve"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Memory_Pointer_Ops/tl.advance.md:34
msgid ""
"- Ascend еҜ№жҜ” GPU зјәеӨұuint8гҖҒuint16гҖҒuint32гҖҒuint64гҖҒfp64зҡ„ж”ҜжҢҒиғҪеҠӣпјҲзЎ¬д»¶йҷҗеҲ¶пјүгҖӮ\n"
"- AscendеҸӘе…Ғи®ёйҖҡиҝҮи°ғж•ҙ`order`еҸӮж•°зҡ„йЎәеәҸжқҘиЎЁиҫҫиҪ¬зҪ®иҜӯд№үпјҢдёҚиғҪйҖҡиҝҮи°ғж•ҙ`stride`еҸӮж•°зҡ„йЎәеәҸе®һзҺ°иҪ¬зҪ®иҜӯд№үгҖӮ\n"
"- еҪ“еүҚ`tl.make_tensor_ptr`пјҢеҰӮжһңдёҺиҫғеӨҚжқӮзҡ„еҫӘзҺҜе’ҢеҲҶж”ҜиҜӯеҸҘжҗӯй…ҚдҪҝз”ЁпјҢеҸҜиғҪдјҡеҮәзҺ°зј–иҜ‘й—®йўҳ\n"
msgstr ""
"- Ascend lacks support for uint8, uint16, uint32, uint64, and fp64 compared to GPU (hardware limitation).\n"
"- Ascend only allows expressing transpose semantics by adjusting the order of the `order` parameter, not by adjusting the order of the `stride` parameter.\n"
"- Currently, `tl.make_tensor_ptr` may encounter compilation issues when used with complex loop and branch statements.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Memory_Pointer_Ops/tl.advance.md:36
msgid "### 2.4 дҪҝз”Ёж–№жі•"
msgstr "### 2.4 Usage"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Memory_Pointer_Ops/tl.advance.md:38
msgid "еҸӮиҖғд»ҘдёӢзӨәдҫӢпјҡ"
msgstr "Refer to the following example:"

#. type: code
#: docs/zh/triton_api/Memory_Pointer_Ops/tl.advance.md:40
msgid ""
"```python\n"
"@triton.jit\n"
"def fn_npu_3d(output_ptr, x_ptr, y_ptr, z_ptr, output_ptr1, XB: tl.constexpr, YB: tl.constexpr, ZB: tl.constexpr):\n"
"    block_ptr_in = tl.make_block_ptr(\n"
"        base=x_ptr,\n"
"        shape=(XB, YB, ZB),\n"
"        strides=(YB * ZB, ZB, 1),\n"
"        offsets=(3, 1, 2),\n"
"        block_shape=(XB, YB, ZB),\n"
"        order=(2, 1, 0),\n"
"    )\n"
"    bbptr = tl.advance(block_ptr_in, (-3, -1, -2))\n"
"    # XB,YB,1\n"
"    X = tl.load(bbptr)\n"
"\n"
"    block_ptr_out = tl.make_block_ptr(\n"
"        base=output_ptr,\n"
"        shape=(XB, YB, ZB),\n"
"        strides=(YB * ZB, ZB, 1),\n"
"        offsets=(0, 0, 0),\n"
"        block_shape=(XB, YB, ZB),\n"
"        order=(2, 1, 0),\n"
"    )\n"
"    tl.store(block_ptr_out, X)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

